				<name type="primary" sortindex="4" value="La Scamorra" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>An abstract 1vs1 strategy game inspired by chess, roshambo (AKA RockPaperScissors), traditional italian card games and the awesome videogame 'Pawnbarian'.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Game is played on a 5x5 checkerboard and each player has 3 different pieces representing the 3 symbols of Roshambo. &amp;#10;Each player also has a deck of chess cards to play.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Similar to a trump game each player has a 3 cards hand from which, in turn, they play a card. They then proceed to move one of their pieces according to the chess moving scheme represented on the card (if you play a bishop you can move any of your pieces as if it was a bishop).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Pieces are captured the same way you do in chess, but following the roshambo logic (eg: a scissor piece can only capture a paper piece).&amp;#10;After a player has moved he draws another card and the turn passes to his opponent.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Pieces  captured can be respawned in game using special cards and every capture is a point.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;After 15 turns the game ends and the player with the highest score wins. If a player is able to capture all 3 pieces of his opponent before he is able to respawn any of them the game ends immediately by knockout.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Full rules and manual can be found on the official Scamorra site.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
